# WorkVouch Design System

The **Live Demo** (`/demo`, `components/demo-center/`) defines the official WorkVouch visual language. Production must match it.

## Canonical components

Use `@/components/wv` for all new UI:

- `WvShell` / `WvContainer` — page canvas + max-width
- `WvCard` — glass cards
- `WvButton` — CTAs
- `WvPageHeader` — page titles
- `WvTrustScore` — trust score visualization
- `WvBadge`, `WvInput`, `WvStatCard`
- Motion: `pageTransition`, `staggerItem` from `@/components/wv`

Legacy `components/ui/button` and `components/ui/card` are aligned to dark glass — prefer `Wv*` for new code.

## Visual rules

- **Dark-first**: background `#0a0a0f`, glass surfaces `bg-wv-surface`, borders `border-wv-border`
- **Brand color sparingly**: blue/green for CTAs, trust scores, links, charts — not full-page fills
- **Typography**: large headlines, `text-wv-muted` body, generous spacing
- **Icons**: Lucide only (`lucide-react`)
- **Motion**: Framer Motion — subtle fades, never distracting
- **No bright white pages** unless required for print/PDF

## Layout

- Marketing/auth: `WvShell` + global `Navbar`
- Employee app: `WorkVouchLayoutClient` (dark sidebar + navbar)
- Demo: `DemoShell` (hides global navbar)
- Every page: `WvContainer` or `max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6`

## Before shipping any screen

Ask: *Would this look at home inside `/demo`?* If not, redesign using `Wv*` components.

## Do not

- Duplicate card/button styles inline
- Use light-gray marketing pages (`bg-gray-50`, white cards) on user-facing routes
- Mix Heroicons and Lucide on the same screen (Lucide preferred)
- Remove functionality when restyling
